~ start
To be honest, I feel a lot of envy towards many people, including those I'm close to.
A lot of my gamedev friends have started being part of large teams, leading teams of their own, and even publishing commercial games on Steam.
Even outside of gamedev, I've had a lot of creative people achieve great things, including having sizable projects and profiting handsomely off of commissions.
Meanwhile I'm here, chasing deadlines, struggling at a job I don't like, and scrambling together to make this game after I spent most of the jam time with exams and finals.
It's... hard not to feel stuck, like I'll never achieve the goals I dreamt of.
=> END